==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plenty
<hw>Plen"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Plenties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, in <au>Shak.</au></plu> <ety>[OE.
<ets>plentee</ets>, <ets>plente</ets>, OF. <ets>plent⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>plenitas</ets>, fr. <ets>plenus</ets> full. See <er>Full</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>, and cf. <er>Complete</er>.]</ety> <def>Full or adequate
supply; enough and to spare; sufficiency; specifically, abundant
productiveness of the earth; ample supply for human wants; abundance;
copiousness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Plenty</xex> of corn and wine.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Gen. xxvii. 28.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Promises Britain peace and
<xex>plenty</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Houses of office stuffed with <qex>plentee</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The teeming clouds Descend in gladsome <qex>plenty</qex> o'er the
world.</q> <rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Abundance; exuberance. See
<er>Abundance</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plenty
<hw>Plen"ty</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Plentiful; abundant.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If reasons were as <qex>plenty</qex> as blackberries.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak. (Folio ed.)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those countries where shrubs are <qex>plenty</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenum</ent>⟦br⟧
